'cont'=>'(Seeing in August the tenth), September 4, 1995, the opening of the Fourth World Conference on Women in Beijing. <br> United Nations Fourth World Conference on Women in Beijing on September 4 the grand opening <br> women has been the focus of attention of the United Nations in the field of social and development. The second year after the founding of the United Nations, the United Nations Economic and Social Council on the establishment of a Commission on the Status of Women, specifically on the pressing issues of women&#39;s rights to study, develop promotion measures. In December 1952, the United Nations adopted the Convention on the Political Rights of Women. 1975 by the United Nations as the \"International Year of Women\", in June this year, the first World Conference on Women held in Mexico City. In July 1980, the United Nations Second World Conference on Women in Copenhagen. Third World Conference on Women held in Nairobi, Kenya, in July 1985, the General Assembly discussed and adopted \"the Nairobi Forward-looking Strategies for the Advancement of Women in 2000\" (referred to as the \"Nairobi Strategy\"). <br> \"Nairobi Strategy is internationally recognized as a programmatic document for the advancement of women, equality, development and peace for the overall goal to achieve gender equality for women around the world in the year 2000 further participation in national development, and safeguarding world peace to develop action-oriented, specific objectives of the program, from a global perspective reflects the world of women in all fields of political, economic, social and cultural requirements and wishes. 10 years to promote and under the influence of the \"Nairobi Strategy, the cause of the world&#39;s women made unprecedented progress. In March 1992, the 36th meeting of the United Nations Commission on the Status of Women to accept the invitation of the Chinese government, the decision of the Fourth World Conference on Women held in Beijing. The theme of the conference is \"Action for Equality, Development and Peace\"; sub-theme is \"education, health and employment. The purpose of this conference is: comprehensive monitoring of the implementation of the review and appraisal of the Nairobi Strategy \", the international community and governments to promote renewed political commitment, action for equality, development and peace. September 4, 1995, the grand opening of the United Nations Fourth World Conference on Women in Beijing International Convention Center. Special Representative of the the <br> UN Secretary-General Boutros Boutros-Ghali, the UN Under-Secretary-General Kittani at the opening ceremony on behalf of Gali speech. He pointed out that this meeting has laid a new era of relations between China and the United Nations, is a milestone in the history of the United Nations women&#39;s work, is the climax of a series of global conferences. The meeting elected vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People&#39;s Congress, chairman of the All China Women&#39;s Federation, the FWCW Chinese government delegation head of Chen Muhua any President of the United Nations Fourth World Conference on Women. (Today in History www.lssdjt.com) <br> The World Conference on Women held a total of 16 plenary meeting, representatives from 197 countries and regions, and international organizations, non-governmental organizations on behalf of equality, realistic atmosphere the eradication of poverty, to stop the war, to stop violence against women and eliminate gender inequality started a lively debate, more consistent advice. On September 15, the 12-day Fourth World Conference on Women came to an end after the adoption of the Beijing Declaration and Programme of Action. Designed to accelerate the implementation of the Nairobi Strategy \"Beijing Declaration and Programme of Action\" epitomizes the will and wisdom of the delegates and women, clearly defined task of the world in the next five years, the women&#39;s movement, the goal, is to unite the world women to achieve their own liberation struggle written Declaration and Programme of Action. <br> Fourth World Conference on Women is a grand scale unprecedented in the history of the United Nations, was attended by up to 1.76 million people, there are more than 30,000 people participated in the auxiliary meeting of the World Conference on Women - NGO women Forum. This Congress to improve the status of women in all countries, all peoples, especially the understanding and friendship between the women, to promote the cause of human progress, is of great significance. <br>'
